    {
      "id": "6f997db3f25c9b0f841e4fd738cbc0b58d16209c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-01 06:40:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI am a little bit concerned with the fix being \"just shut off the warning\". Instead I think coverity highlight a a piece of code that is more dangerous that that.\n\nIf we get an error mid-execution, we abort right away and that potentially leaves the system in inconsistent state with some configs converted and some not?\n\nArtem, as the original contributor of this code can you please take a look here and perhaps come with or suggest a more consistent fix?\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "25fab51bfcd11745f7d24c930bab8c83e063a1ac",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 257,
        "name": "Keith Mannthey",
        "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
        "username": "kmannth",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-24 01:33:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThere is plenty of places in this code path just jumps to error_out there is such an example for mgs_find_or_make_fsdb: It cerrors and exits out. \n\nI would not mind an CERROR explaining the situation like the rest of the section of code but I am not quite sure what you are trying to get at Oleg?\n\nCovertly likely found an unused return by the functions.  name_create and name_create_mdt can fail but we were not checking. \n\nArtem, do you have any thoughts about the proper way to exit on errors in these sots?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "629674d07fd037aef382701c9bf32dd75fa69a4a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 202,
        "name": "Artem Blagodarenko",
        "email": "artem_blagodarenko@xyratex.com",
        "username": "Artem_Blagodarenko",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-24 04:29:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe right way to exit from that loop is restore all changed files. I am working under right cleanup now. Thanks, that you point on this problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
